DemucsProcessingCapability.separate_vocals

def separate_vocals(
    audio:Union, # Path to the input audio (full-band; NOT model-ready)
    output_dir:str, # Adapter-chosen dir to write the artifact into
    kwargs:VAR_KEYWORD
)-&gt;SourceSeparationResult: # Vocals-isolated artifact + metadata

Extract the vocals stem from an audio file — PURE COMPUTE.
Stage 8 / PILLAR 1c: the cache-check + the (input,config)-&gt;output_dir choice + persistence moved to the generic adapter (cjm-source-separation-adapter-interface); this method loads the model, runs separation, WRITES the vocals stem (+ optional other stems) into the adapter-supplied output_dir, and returns the typed result. Separation params come from self.config (no per-call kwarg override — the tool runs its effective config). SG-47 Track B maps a CUDA OOM at the inference site to CapabilityResourceError (CR-7 reactive-retry reloads).
